tldr: The user requested a thorough review and improvement of their sleep
  questionnaire app's aesthetics. I implemented a comprehensive visual redesign,
  transforming the app from a generic look to a calming, professional, and
  sleep-themed experience with refined colors, layouts, and interactive
  elements.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was functional but lacked visual
  sophistication. I began by conducting a detailed analysis of the existing
  design, identifying areas such as the generic color palette, plain
  backgrounds, and basic form elements as key opportunities for improvement. The
  approach involved a multi-faceted redesign, starting with a new, calming
  sleep-themed color palette and custom utility classes. I then systematically
  updated the main questionnaire form, introducing subtle background blurs, a
  redesigned progress indicator, and a star pattern overlay on card headers. The
  welcome screen was transformed with a hero section and interactive feature
  cards, while all core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and
  sliders received significant visual polish. Finally, I ensured consistent
  styling across all questionnaire sections and the report, replacing old gray
  boxes with refined card-style groupings. The outcome is a visually cohesive,
  professional, and inviting application that aligns with the serene nature of
  sleep health assessment.
